<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Eio on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/eio/</link><description>Recent content in Eio on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en</language><atom:link href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/eio/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>[Solution] C Input/output error: EIO</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/c/input-output-error/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/c/input-output-error/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="inputoutput-error-eio"&gt;Input/output error: EIO&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;EIO is a generic I/O error indicating the kernel encountered a problem communicating with hardware or a driver. This is often unrecoverable.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-c" data-lang="c"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 1: Disk hardware failure
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;read&lt;/span&gt;(fd, buf, &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;100&lt;/span&gt;); &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// EIO — bad disk sector
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 2: Corrupted filesystem
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;read&lt;/span&gt;(fd, buf, &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;100&lt;/span&gt;); &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// EIO — filesystem damage
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 3: Device driver error
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;read&lt;/span&gt;(fd, buf, &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;100&lt;/span&gt;); &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// EIO — driver problem
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="fix-1-check-hardware"&gt;Fix 1: Check hardware&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;dmesg | grep -i error
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;smartctl -a /dev/sda
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-2-check-filesystem"&gt;Fix 2: Check filesystem&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;fsck /dev/sda1
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# or&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;e2fsck -f /dev/sda1
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-3-retry-the-operation"&gt;Fix 3: Retry the operation&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-c" data-lang="c"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;for&lt;/span&gt; (&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; i &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;0&lt;/span&gt;; i &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;3&lt;/span&gt;; i&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;++&lt;/span&gt;) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;ssize_t&lt;/span&gt; result &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;read&lt;/span&gt;(fd, buf, size);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (result &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;0&lt;/span&gt;) &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;break&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (errno &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;!=&lt;/span&gt; EIO) &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;break&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;usleep&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1000&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;*&lt;/span&gt; (&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt; i)); &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// exponential backoff
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="related-errors"&gt;Related Errors&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/c/bad-file-descriptor/"&gt;Bad file descriptor&lt;/a&gt; — EBADF.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/c/input-output-error/"&gt;Input/output error&lt;/a&gt; — detailed analysis.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/c/read-only-file-system/"&gt;Read-only file system&lt;/a&gt; — EROFS.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] Linux EIO (errno 5) — Input/Output Error Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/os/linux/errno-5/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/os/linux/errno-5/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="linux-eio-errno-5--inputoutput-error"&gt;Linux EIO (errno 5) — Input/Output Error&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;EIO (errno 5) is a low-level error indicating that the kernel encountered an input/output failure during a system call. This typically means the storage hardware, device driver, or filesystem layer failed to read from or write to a storage device. Unlike higher-level errors, EIO often signals a serious hardware or deep filesystem problem that requires immediate attention.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Failing or dead hard drive or SSD&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Corrupted filesystem&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Faulty or loose SATA/NVMe cable&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bad sectors on the disk&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;USB drive failure or disconnection during I/O&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;RAID array degradation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;NFS server unreachable&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Device driver bugs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix-eio"&gt;How to Fix EIO&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="1-check-kernel-ring-buffer-for-errors"&gt;1. Check Kernel Ring Buffer for Errors&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The kernel log often reveals the root cause before you see EIO:&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>